editorialNotes.standard: Bursting with beats and energy, Toca Dance will make the whole family want to get up and groove. This incredibly cute game puts kids in charge of their own musical productionâchoosing dancers, costumes and techno tracks, and choreographing moves using simple swipes and taps. Once the performance starts, the real fun begins: you can fling items at the stage, set off pyrotechnics and other cool effects and even cheer (or boo) your squad. Seeing the payoffâan awesome video you can shareâwill encourage players to jump right back in and start working on their next great show.

editorialNotes.standard: Slide a shape into the correct holeâeasy, right? It is, at first. But what makes Busy Shapes so clever is the way it gently gets more challenging, motivating little kids to find solutions to each puzzle through experimentation. From shape-changing to colour-mixing to hidden holes, weâre impressed with how the gameplay spurs out-of-the-box thinking, stimulating curious young minds.

editorialNotes.standard: See the beauty and power of ABCs in an app where every letter holds secret words. Touch an F, and it sprouts a foot, then feathers, then a fan; a G becomes a guitar in a garden with ghosts. Kids will love poking and prodding their way to the end of the alphabet, while parents will dig the unpredictability and gorgeous animation in this Apple Design Award winner.
editorialNotes.short: Interactive alphabet learning where words and letters come to life.
